75 % of the professional working mothers have had problems because of their babies
discrimination in the workplace has risen in recent years , especially for women , young people who want to be mothers .
reveals that the study " fertility and women 's professional career in spain , " carried out by the csic together with the instituto de mujer .
the survey , conducted on 9 737 women 15 to 75 , leaves no room for doubt : 75 % of working mothers have seen their careers restricted because of the babies .
the study indicates that there are many differences regarding the beginning of life in a partnership , and the number of children , whether or not the woman works and occupied the kind of job .
those who do not have to work outside the home , work part time or have a stable job little , reached earlier in a partnership , and have more children have their first pregnancy earlier .
however , women who have a stable job , mostly in the public sector , to postpone the entry in life in a partnership and the first pregnancy , and have fewer children .
women aged between 35 and 49 with a fixed work have their first child , on average , 3.7 years after having built in couple . that figure rises to 4.1 among those who work in the public sector . " these data show that women have a stable job requiring more time in their lives for that , which led them to reject the union and the arrival of the children .
more broadly , the type of job wielded influence the maternity leave , but less common starting date of life , " explains the chercheuse csic margarita delgado .
the level of education is another factor that widening the gap of the age of the marriage of women and their first child .
according to the survey , the higher the level of education , the more they marient and have their first child later .
the difference remains as among the women of the same generation .
for example , in a group of between 35 and 49 years , those who have made elementary and higher studies have been mothers respectively for the first time to 25,1 and 32,1 years on average .
" another disctinction is also among the women , according to the level of education .
while those who carry out the basic studies marient and have their first child before to find a stable job , those studies of higher average level or reverse the programme and give priority to the achievement of a stable job as a condition for marriage and the arrival of a child , " says mrs delgado .
