sales of light commercial vehicles to go
after nearly two years ago , the market of light commercial vehicles is to see some light at the end of the tunnel .
the 9 425 vehicles registered in november in spain is an increase of 12.6 percent in 2008 and , more importantly , they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decline , according to figures by the patronal manufacturers association anfac and ganvam , the dealers .
however , we need to balance the good news , because the reference for the comparison , the november 2008 , was particularly bad , with a reduction of 60 percent compared with the previous year .
therefore , despite the events of the last month , the immatriculations accumulated in the 11 months are 40 percent less than those of the previous year .
since january , if you add all vehicles coming into the category of light commercial vehicles - derived from cars , vans , pick-up fourgons light and light trucks with windows 95 853 have been sold .
high clouds that affect their request did not eliminated . in fact , despite being bought by individuals , most of the purchases are made by small and medium enterprises , which pay in nearly 100 % of the cases with external funding .
and , in addition to the restrictions involved by restricting credit , we need to add other factors such as the rise in the unemployment rate and the continuation of the bad economic situation .
faced with this situation , and in contrast to the cars , the aid to the purchase of the 2000e were used .
as well as individuals , independent and those who wish to acquire a commercial vehicle slightly less than 3.5 tonnes with a level of carbon dioxide emissions , which does not exceed 160 grams per kilometre , can also benefit , but the number of transactions speaks for itself .
yesterday , in ganvam , it recalled once again the need for the government to pay special attention to these vehicles and industrial vehicles , trucks and buses .
the dealers ' association provides a 2010 similar to that end , for which it is a fall in sales - passenger vehicles and the suv of 19 % .
the emergency brake is now required aid
as has occurred with the system anti-lock restrictions abs and it will take place with the esp , stability control systems for emergency aid to brake compulsory will form part of the european cars .
compulsory they are already on the newly registered cars and light commercial vehicles , while for the rest of the vehicles , a period has been set up at the end of february 2011 .
the measure , imposed by the european union , seeks to strengthen the protection of pedestrians action , even if , by the way , it can also help prevent many blows back .
the assistant to the emergency brake is increasing pressure on the brakes in urgent cases detected by the system with the shot in the foot of the driver .
but they do not always maintained the pressure until the end .
according to a study by the manufacturer of components for cars bosch , one third of the drivers involved in an accident did not rely on the brakes before the collision , and half of them did not benefit from its full force .
up to 1 , 100 accidents
intervention of aid , revancha , requires maximum braking system , cutting the distance which needed to stop the car .
according to a study by the eu , if all vehicles were equipped with this type of points , up to 1 100 accidents in which pedestrians are involved could be prevented each year .
this reduction would be even more relevant with the ' popularisation of smart emergency braking systems : it is a sinister on four with the injured would be avoided .
in this case , the vehicle is equipped with a system that with a radar or a camera , detect obstacles and to prevent the driver , in addition to slightly on the brakes .
if the driver is applied , it help in increasing the pressure on the , if it is necessary .
if it does not act , that the crash is inevitable , it has a maximum effort on the checks to minimize the damage .
