a fine of 63 million in france telecom to curb the competition
french competition regulator has imposed a fine of 63 million euros to anti-competitive france telecom for his conduct in the caribbean region of the country .
according to this institution , the operator has restricted competition in fixed and mobile telephony by signing exclusive agreements , prices and consumer loyalty programs on the fringes of the regulation .
with this step , the former french monopoly and state company , is still more than 450 million euros in fines since 1994 , because it puts obstacles to its competitors .
the sanctioning yesterday has been increased because the authority that ensures the competition believes that france telecom has made similar crimes in the past and it is therefore repeat offender .
